<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-11T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="278" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860H.01/7–1145: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Yugoslavia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Shantz</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-11T19:00:00-04:00">July 11,
                                    1945—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>192. Dept has noted widely quoted press reports of statement attributed
                            to Marshal Tito on July 8 accusing Greek forces of firing across
                            Greek-Yugoslav border “to provoke us”. Similar accusations published
                            previously in Belgrade have also come to Dept’s attention.</p>
                        <p>Please inform FonOff that no information from other sources has <pb facs="0333" n="321" xml:id="pg_321"/> been received by Dept to
                            substantiate these statements and this Govt will appreciate any data
                            Yugoslav authorities can furnish.</p>
                        <p>Sent to Belgrade, repeated to London, Moscow and Athens.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>